{"type":"message","id":"537bd1df","parentId":"e011f1d0","timestamp":"2026-02-24T01:44:03.882Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] True if we brute-force it. But we don’t need infinite generation—we fake infinity with **deterministic sampling** + **on-demand compute**.\n\nDo it like this:\n- Precompute cheap skeletons with small/local models\n- Only call Claude for “zoomed-in” high-value branches\n- Cache everything by hash (same query never pays twice)\n- Use progressive reveal: show 100 now, generate next 900 only if user keeps exploring\n\nSo the product *feels* Babel-infinite while spend stays bounded. Want me to sketch a ruthless cost model (MVP monthly budget tiers: $50 / $200 / $1k)?","textSignature":"msg_0955db6ac92c349501699d025fed808196b1503ad581835752"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":371,"output":142,"cacheRead":19456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19969,"cost":{"input":0.00064925,"output":0.001988,"cacheRead":0.0034048,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00604205}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771897438996}}
