{"type":"message","id":"e6d7d10c","parentId":"7c58c24b","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:29:51.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucian is saying the tweet reply is blocked now - meaning replying to tweets from accounts that haven't engaged with us is a limitation we keep hitting. This is likely because our account doesn't have enough engagement/followers yet, or because X has restrictions on replying to tweets from accounts that haven't interacted with us. Let me think about this...\n\nActually the 403 error says \"Reply to this conversation is not allowed because you have not been mentioned or otherwise engaged by the author of the post you are replying to.\" This is an X API restriction - you can only reply to tweets where the author has mentioned or engaged with you. This is a platform-level restriction to prevent spam.\n\nSo we can only reply to:\n\n\n1. Tweets that mention @CorvusLatimer\n2. Tweets from accounts that have previously engaged with us (liked, replied, retweeted)\n\nThis is a significant limitation for our engagement strategy. We need to find other ways to engage - like quote tweeting instead of direct replies, or posting standalone responses. Let me confirm my understanding with Lucian.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Yeah — X restricts replies to accounts that haven't engaged with us first. Been hitting it a few times tonight. We can still quote tweet or post standalone takes on the same topic, just can't thread directly into their conversation. Annoying limitation but workable."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":10,"output":305,"cacheRead":77392,"cacheWrite":168,"totalTokens":77875,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.004575,"cacheRead":0.023217599999999998,"cacheWrite":0.00063,"total":0.028452599999999995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772047781751}}
