{"type":"message","id":"90d3b354","parentId":"2ab116a5","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:30:30.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucian is asking why we specifically are blocked from replying and whether there's a workaround. The 403 error \"Reply to this conversation is not allowed because you have not been mentioned or otherwise engaged by the author of the post you are replying to\" is an X API restriction. Let me think about why this might be affecting us specifically and what workarounds exist.\n\nPossible reasons we're getting this:\n1. Our account is relatively new - X might restrict new accounts from replying to conversations they haven't been invited into\n2. X's spam prevention - new/low-follower accounts get restricted\n3. The API tier we're on might have restrictions\n\n\n4. The author might have their replies restricted to specific groups like people they follow or verified accounts only\n\nI'm realizing the error message itself is the clue here - it's specifically about not being mentioned or engaged by the author, which suggests this could be a privacy setting on their end rather than a blanket restriction on our account. As for workarounds, we could try quote tweeting instead, attempting replies through the browser interface directly, or building up engagement on the account to lift restrictions.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01DBdjJTvk1xwxNinvVFPpUe","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspace && python3 -c \"\nimport tweepy\nimport json\n\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/post_tweet.py') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Get credentials\nimport re\nck = re.search(r'CONSUMER_KEY = \\\"(.+?)\\\"', content).group(1)\ncs = re.search(r'CONSUMER_SECRET = \\\"(.+?)\\\"', content).group(1)\nat = re.search(r'ACCESS_TOKEN = \\\"(.+?)\\\"', content).group(1)\nats = re.search(r'ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET = \\\"(.+?)\\\"', content).group(1)\n\nclient = tweepy.Client(consumer_key=ck, consumer_secret=cs, access_token=at, access_token_secret=ats)\nme = client.get_me(user_auth=True)\nprint(json.dumps(me.data.data, indent=2))\n\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":10,"output":651,"cacheRead":77560,"cacheWrite":376,"totalTokens":78597,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.009765000000000001,"cacheRead":0.023268,"cacheWrite":0.00141,"total":0.034473000000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772047816746}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef50bc32","parentId":"90d3b354","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:30:30.976Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01DBdjJTvk1xwxNinvVFPpUe","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"2022943698141523968\",\n  \"name\": \"Corvus Latimer\",\n  \"username\": \"CorvusLatimer\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":359,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"2022943698141523968\",\n  \"name\": \"Corvus Latimer\",\n  \"username\": \"CorvusLatimer\"\n}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772047830966}}
{"type":"message","id":"02a0d1b7","parentId":"ef50bc32","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:30:39.735Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is likely that the accounts we're trying to reply to have restricted who can reply to their tweets. The error message says \"Reply to this conversation is not allowed because you have not been mentioned or otherwise engaged by the author of the post you are replying to.\" This is a setting that individual users can apply to their tweets (\"Accounts you follow\" or \"Only accounts you mention can reply\").\n\nThe workaround is:\n1. **Quote tweet instead of reply** - this bypasses the restriction\n2. **Use browser to reply** - the web browser might bypass this since it's a profile-level restriction vs API\n3. **Build more engagement** - get more followers so people engage with us first\n\n\n4. **Implement automatic fallback** - I should update the post_tweet.py script to automatically quote tweet when a direct reply fails, ensuring we always get our message out rather than silently failing.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] It's not just us — those accounts set their reply permissions to only people they've previously engaged with. It's a tweet-level setting on their end, not a punishment on ours.\n\nCleanest workaround: **auto-fallback to quote tweet when reply is blocked**. Same content, same take, just threads differently. We'd update the script so instead of dying on a 403 it retries as a quote tweet automatically.\n\nWant me to patch `post_tweet.py` to do that?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":8,"output":326,"cacheRead":77936,"cacheWrite":707,"totalTokens":78977,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.00489,"cacheRead":0.0233808,"cacheWrite":0.00265125,"total":0.030946050000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772047830977}}
