{"type":"message","id":"6900b84d","parentId":"51ecb416","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:35:22.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucian is confirming the strategy - post on our main timeline and include a link to the tweet we're responding to, as a quote tweet or standalone post with the tweet URL included. That's exactly how quote tweeting works. Let me confirm and patch the script.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Yeah exactly — quote tweet pulls their tweet into our post so people still see the context, plus it hits our own followers. Let me patch the script now so it does this automatically on a 403."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01BjJHMRv95XTvzQXuhbP4nt","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/post_tweet.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":10,"output":173,"cacheRead":79640,"cacheWrite":507,"totalTokens":80330,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.002595,"cacheRead":0.023892,"cacheWrite":0.00190125,"total":0.02841825}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772048112040}}
{"type":"message","id":"66de5450","parentId":"6900b84d","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:35:22.349Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01BjJHMRv95XTvzQXuhbP4nt","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nPost to X (Twitter) using Tweepy with OAuth 1.0a\nUsage: \n  python3 post_tweet.py \"Your tweet text here\"\n  python3 post_tweet.py --reply-to TWEET_ID \"Your reply text\"\n\"\"\"\n\nimport tweepy\nimport sys\nimport argparse\n\n# OAuth 1.0a credentials\nCONSUMER_KEY = \"cmkQJHO2WHsS4KoJwLwq1jCeg\"\nCONSUMER_SECRET = \"U2HPYcR5NtoZtQmVsiNyjobh6lmIsU0PwG2lMMTN8Szg8klGFS\"\nACCESS_TOKEN = \"2022943698141523968-ARzK1448e7oVhiEKDnnfQi2EWNOwCB\"\nACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET = \"TYllZTKxT9GIZrrU8znBCeAYtys6Szr83asQDqQhH7Hjg\"\n\ndef post_tweet(text, reply_to=None):\n    \"\"\"Post a tweet or reply using Tweepy v2\"\"\"\n    try:\n        # Authenticate using v2 Client\n        client = tweepy.Client(\n            consumer_key=CONSUMER_KEY,\n            consumer_secret=CONSUMER_SECRET,\n            access_token=ACCESS_TOKEN,\n            access_token_secret=ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET\n        )\n        \n        # Post tweet using v2 API\n        if reply_to:\n            response = client.create_tweet(text=text, in_reply_to_tweet_id=reply_to)\n        else:\n            response = client.create_tweet(text=text)\n            \n        tweet_id = response.data['id']\n        \n        if reply_to:\n            print(f\"✅ Reply posted successfully!\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"✅ Tweet posted successfully!\")\n        print(f\"URL: https://x.com/CorvusLatimer/status/{tweet_id}\")\n        return response\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"❌ Error posting tweet: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='Post a tweet or reply to X')\n    parser.add_argument('text', help='Tweet text')\n    parser.add_argument('--reply-to', help='Tweet ID to reply to', default=None)\n    \n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    post_tweet(args.text, args.reply_to)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772048122342}}
{"type":"message","id":"17a26c18","parentId":"66de5450","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:35:37.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to update the script to auto-fallback to a quote tweet when a reply is blocked with a 403. The way to quote tweet is to include the tweet URL at the end of the text. Let me update the script.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01HCJseK8rTyfFAyQQLxQhG5","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/post_tweet.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nPost to X (Twitter) using Tweepy with OAuth 1.0a\nUsage: \n  python3 post_tweet.py \"Your tweet text here\"\n  python3 post_tweet.py --reply-to TWEET_ID \"Your reply text\"\n\nIf a reply is blocked (403 - author hasn't engaged us), auto-falls back to a quote tweet.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport tweepy\nimport sys\nimport argparse\n\n# OAuth 1.0a credentials\nCONSUMER_KEY = \"cmkQJHO2WHsS4KoJwLwq1jCeg\"\nCONSUMER_SECRET = \"U2HPYcR5NtoZtQmVsiNyjobh6lmIsU0PwG2lMMTN8Szg8klGFS\"\nACCESS_TOKEN = \"2022943698141523968-ARzK1448e7oVhiEKDnnfQi2EWNOwCB\"\nACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET = \"TYllZTKxT9GIZrrU8znBCeAYtys6Szr83asQDqQhH7Hjg\"\n\ndef post_tweet(text, reply_to=None, quote_tweet_id=None):\n    \"\"\"Post a tweet, reply, or quote tweet using Tweepy v2\"\"\"\n    client = tweepy.Client(\n        consumer_key=CONSUMER_KEY,\n        consumer_secret=CONSUMER_SECRET,\n        access_token=ACCESS_TOKEN,\n        access_token_secret=ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET\n    )\n\n    # If reply_to is set, try reply first — fallback to quote tweet on 403\n    if reply_to:\n        try:\n            response = client.create_tweet(text=text, in_reply_to_tweet_id=reply_to)\n            tweet_id = response.data['id']\n            print(f\"✅ Reply posted successfully!\")\n            print(f\"URL: https://x.com/CorvusLatimer/status/{tweet_id}\")\n            return response\n        except tweepy.errors.Forbidden as e:\n            err = str(e)\n            if \"not allowed\" in err or \"403\" in err or \"mentioned\" in err.lower():\n                print(f\"⚠️  Reply blocked (author restriction). Falling back to quote tweet...\")\n                quote_tweet_id = reply_to\n            else:\n                print(f\"❌ Error posting reply: {e}\")\n                sys.exit(1)\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"❌ Error posting reply: {e}\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\n    # Quote tweet — append the URL to the text\n    if quote_tweet_id:\n        quote_url = f\"https://x.com/i/web/status/{quote_tweet_id}\"\n        full_text = f\"{text} {quote_url}\"\n        try:\n            response = client.create_tweet(text=full_text)\n            tweet_id = response.data['id']\n            print(f\"✅ Quote tweet posted successfully!\")\n            print(f\"URL: https://x.com/CorvusLatimer/status/{tweet_id}\")\n            return response\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"❌ Error posting quote tweet: {e}\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\n    # Plain tweet\n    try:\n        response = client.create_tweet(text=text)\n        tweet_id = response.data['id']\n        print(f\"✅ Tweet posted successfully!\")\n        print(f\"URL: https://x.com/CorvusLatimer/status/{tweet_id}\")\n        return response\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"❌ Error posting tweet: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='Post a tweet, reply, or quote tweet to X')\n    parser.add_argument('text', help='Tweet text')\n    parser.add_argument('--reply-to', help='Tweet ID to reply to (auto-falls back to quote tweet if blocked)', default=None)\n    parser.add_argument('--quote', help='Tweet ID to quote tweet directly', default=None)\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    post_tweet(args.text, reply_to=args.reply_to, quote_tweet_id=args.quote)\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":8,"output":1206,"cacheRead":80147,"cacheWrite":834,"totalTokens":82195,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.018090000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0240441,"cacheWrite":0.0031275,"total":0.0452856}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772048122351}}
