{"type":"message","id":"74bad3e9","parentId":"a9b6127e","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:48:12.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that I'm appending the URL `https://x.com/i/web/status/{tweet_id}` but to make it show as a quote tweet embed in the X UI, I need to use the correct tweet URL format: `https://twitter.com/username/status/tweet_id` or `https://x.com/username/status/tweet_id`. The `/i/web/status/` URL format might be causing it to not render as a proper quote tweet.\n\nActually, for the Tweepy v2 API, there's a `quote_tweet_id` parameter in `create_tweet()`. Let me check if that's supported.\n\nLooking at the Tweepy docs, `client.create_tweet()` does support a `quote_tweet_id` parameter. \n\nI should use the `quote_tweet_id` parameter directly instead of appending a URL—that's the proper way to create a native quote tweet through the Twitter v2 API, which will render the embed correctly rather than just creating a link.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_018Ph6J5hi9sptLWXoSoMKuk","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/post_tweet.py","offset":40,"limit":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":10,"output":378,"cacheRead":82634,"cacheWrite":151,"totalTokens":83173,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.0056700000000000006,"cacheRead":0.0247902,"cacheWrite":0.00056625,"total":0.03105645}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772048879683}}
