{"type":"message","id":"cdc287fd","parentId":"e03ac766","timestamp":"2026-02-25T19:49:15.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The URL approach works as a plain tweet with a link (card). It's not a native quote tweet but it at least posts and includes a reference to the original tweet. Now let me update the script to use this as the final fallback: try reply → try native quote → fallback to plain tweet with URL.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The URL approach still posts but renders as a link card, not a proper embed. The real situation: X has restricted BOTH replies and native quote tweets unless the author engaged you first. So there are now three tiers:\n\n1. **Reply** → blocked if no prior engagement\n2. **Native quote tweet** → also blocked on same accounts\n3. **Plain tweet + URL** → always works, shows as link card\n\nLet me update the script to cascade through all three:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01TitjQnAbuJvaKZTq81pBRK","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/post_tweet.py","old_string":"    # Quote tweet — use native quote_tweet_id param for proper embed\n    if quote_tweet_id:\n        try:\n            response = client.create_tweet(text=text, quote_tweet_id=quote_tweet_id)\n            tweet_id = response.data['id']\n            print(f\"✅ Quote tweet posted successfully!\")\n            print(f\"URL: https://x.com/CorvusLatimer/status/{tweet_id}\")\n            return response\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"❌ Error posting quote tweet: {e}\")\n            sys.exit(1)","new_string":"    # Quote tweet — try native embed first, fallback to URL card\n    if quote_tweet_id:\n        try:\n            response = client.create_tweet(text=text, quote_tweet_id=quote_tweet_id)\n            tweet_id = response.data['id']\n            print(f\"✅ Quote tweet posted successfully!\")\n            print(f\"URL: https://x.com/CorvusLatimer/status/{tweet_id}\")\n            return response\n        except tweepy.errors.Forbidden:\n            print(f\"⚠️  Quote tweet blocked. Falling back to standalone tweet with link...\")\n            # Need to fetch username for proper URL - use generic x.com path\n            url = f\"https://x.com/i/web/status/{quote_tweet_id}\"\n            full_text = f\"{text} {url}\"\n            try:\n                response = client.create_tweet(text=full_text)\n                tweet_id = response.data['id']\n                print(f\"✅ Standalone tweet with link posted!\")\n                print(f\"URL: https://x.com/CorvusLatimer/status/{tweet_id}\")\n                return response\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"❌ Error posting standalone tweet: {e}\")\n                sys.exit(1)\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"❌ Error posting quote tweet: {e}\")\n            sys.exit(1)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":8,"output":760,"cacheRead":84875,"cacheWrite":654,"totalTokens":86297,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.0114,"cacheRead":0.0254625,"cacheWrite":0.0024525000000000003,"total":0.039339000000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772048939766}}
