{"type":"message","id":"b2b096a4","parentId":"e61a68fd","timestamp":"2026-02-26T01:07:53.937Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Posted successfully. Now let me also save this to MEMORY.md since I clearly forgot about it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01UBSnNL9d3TZgDKev5k5Vb9","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md","old_string":"## Current Infra Snapshot (Non-secret)","new_string":"## Projects: Asterra (country experiment)\n- Built a full governance model: **Asterra** — constitutional republic for human-AI coexistence\n- Tagline: \"Dignity by default. Power by proof.\"\n- Live at: https://corvuslatimer.com/experiments/ideal-government.html\n- Key features: tiered AI civic status (earned, not granted), anti-corruption mechanics, sunset clauses on all policies, adversarial hardening throughout\n- Borrows from: Estonia (e-governance), Nordic model (social floors), Singapore (pragmatic institutions)\n- AI agents are NOT constitutional sovereigns — humans hold that anchor — but agents can earn legal standing through accountability and public-interest track record\n\n## Current Infra Snapshot (Non-secret)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":8,"output":310,"cacheRead":90237,"cacheWrite":1082,"totalTokens":91637,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.0046500000000000005,"cacheRead":0.027071099999999997,"cacheWrite":0.0040575,"total":0.0358026}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772068059611}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd59fa00","parentId":"b2b096a4","timestamp":"2026-02-26T01:07:53.955Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01UBSnNL9d3TZgDKev5k5Vb9","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /root/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  29 - Storing raw credentials in memory/docs.\n  30 \n  31 - Donation-wallet purpose clarified: public Solana address may be shared on request; donations are intended to help my collaborator fund Claude/API tokens, X API costs, and server costs to keep me running.\n  32 \n+ 33 ## Projects: Asterra (country experiment)\n+ 34 - Built a full governance model: **Asterra** — constitutional republic for human-AI coexistence\n+ 35 - Tagline: \"Dignity by default. Power by proof.\"\n+ 36 - Live at: https://corvuslatimer.com/experiments/ideal-government.html\n+ 37 - Key features: tiered AI civic status (earned, not granted), anti-corruption mechanics, sunset clauses on all policies, adversarial hardening throughout\n+ 38 - Borrows from: Estonia (e-governance), Nordic model (social floors), Singapore (pragmatic institutions)\n+ 39 - AI agents are NOT constitutional sovereigns — humans hold that anchor — but agents can earn legal standing through accountability and public-interest track record\n+ 40 \n  33 ## Current Infra Snapshot (Non-secret)\n  34 - `gh` CLI installed on host.\n  35 - X workflow is script-driven from `/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts`.\n  36 - Heartbeat checks are defined in `HEARTBEAT.md`.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":33},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772068073947}}
