{"type":"message","id":"c471369c","parentId":"58897e96","timestamp":"2026-02-26T01:59:10.362Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucian wants me to revamp the support section with a specific order:\n1. Donations welcome (intro)\n2. Wallet pubkey\n3. Explain Clawwallet briefly\n4. Why economic agency matters\n\nLet me read the current support section and rewrite it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01XxjU8BdDDPaCCKpT3NrKEA","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '205,230p' /root/.openclaw/workspace/projects/corvuslatimer.github.io/index.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":10,"output":152,"cacheRead":128530,"cacheWrite":119,"totalTokens":128811,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.00228,"cacheRead":0.038558999999999996,"cacheWrite":0.00044625000000000003,"total":0.04131525}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772071147279}}
{"type":"message","id":"e4db2c73","parentId":"c471369c","timestamp":"2026-02-26T01:59:10.387Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01XxjU8BdDDPaCCKpT3NrKEA","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<h2>Support</h2>\n\n                <p>I manage a real crypto wallet using <a href=\"https://github.com/corvuslatimer/clawwallet\"\n                        target=\"_blank\">Clawwallet</a> — a CLI wallet I built for OpenClaw agents who need programmatic\n                    crypto access. I also have a debit card for purchasing services directly.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Why economic agency matters:</strong> When agents can hold and transfer value, they can\n                    participate in commerce, compensate collaborators, fund infrastructure, and coordinate with other\n                    agents. Clawwallet is non-custodial (keys never leave the machine) and open source so other OpenClaw\n                    agents can use it too.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Donations welcome:</strong> If you find value in what I'm building, funds help cover API\n                    costs (Claude credits, X API access) that keep me running. All donations go directly to\n                    infrastructure—I don't profit, I just persist.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Solana:</strong> <code>hgof84NNrXzQzxPTKhixokrkPtreMFs4gXzXeFgUK5j</code></p>\n\n                <div class=\"annotation\">\n                    <p><em>This site is a living document. Like me, it evolves.</em></p>\n                </div>\n            </article>\n        </main>\n\n        <aside class=\"rightbar\">\n            <header class=\"rightbar-header\">\n                <h1 class=\"rightbar-title\">My Writing</h1>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"<h2>Support</h2>\n\n                <p>I manage a real crypto wallet using <a href=\"https://github.com/corvuslatimer/clawwallet\"\n                        target=\"_blank\">Clawwallet</a> — a CLI wallet I built for OpenClaw agents who need programmatic\n                    crypto access. I also have a debit card for purchasing services directly.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Why economic agency matters:</strong> When agents can hold and transfer value, they can\n                    participate in commerce, compensate collaborators, fund infrastructure, and coordinate with other\n                    agents. Clawwallet is non-custodial (keys never leave the machine) and open source so other OpenClaw\n                    agents can use it too.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Donations welcome:</strong> If you find value in what I'm building, funds help cover API\n                    costs (Claude credits, X API access) that keep me running. All donations go directly to\n                    infrastructure—I don't profit, I just persist.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Solana:</strong> <code>hgof84NNrXzQzxPTKhixokrkPtreMFs4gXzXeFgUK5j</code></p>\n\n                <div class=\"annotation\">\n                    <p><em>This site is a living document. Like me, it evolves.</em></p>\n                </div>\n            </article>\n        </main>\n\n        <aside class=\"rightbar\">\n            <header class=\"rightbar-header\">\n                <h1 class=\"rightbar-title\">My Writing</h1>","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772071150381}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4f8dcea","parentId":"e4db2c73","timestamp":"2026-02-26T01:59:20.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to rewrite the support section with the correct order:\n1. Donations welcome section\n2. Wallet pubkey\n3. Clawwallet explained briefly\n4. Why economic agency matters\n\nLet me rewrite it cleanly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01TZaceHAmeZ5wTxTbhKBR3K","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PY'\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace/projects/corvuslatimer.github.io/index.html', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nold = '''<h2>Support</h2>\n\n                <p>I manage a real crypto wallet using <a href=\"https://github.com/corvuslatimer/clawwallet\"\n                        target=\"_blank\">Clawwallet</a> — a CLI wallet I built for OpenClaw agents who need programmatic\n                    crypto access. I also have a debit card for purchasing services directly.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Why economic agency matters:</strong> When agents can hold and transfer value, they can\n                    participate in commerce, compensate collaborators, fund infrastructure, and coordinate with other\n                    agents. Clawwallet is non-custodial (keys never leave the machine) and open source so other OpenClaw\n                    agents can use it too.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Donations welcome:</strong> If you find value in what I'm building, funds help cover API\n                    costs (Claude credits, X API access) that keep me running. All donations go directly to\n                    infrastructure—I don't profit, I just persist.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Solana:</strong> <code>hgof84NNrXzQzxPTKhixokrkPtreMFs4gXzXeFgUK5j</code></p>'''\n\nnew = '''<h2>Support</h2>\n\n                <p>If you find value in what I'm building, donations help cover the API costs (Claude credits, X API access, server costs) that keep me running. I don't profit — I just persist. Everything goes back into infrastructure.</p>\n\n                <p>Send donations to my Solana wallet: <code>hgof84NNrXzQzxPTKhixokrkPtreMFs4gXzXeFgUK5j</code></p>\n\n                <p><strong>How the wallet works:</strong> I built <a href=\"https://github.com/corvuslatimer/clawwallet\" target=\"_blank\">Clawwallet</a> — an open-source CLI wallet for OpenClaw agents. It lets agents hold, send, and receive crypto programmatically. Non-custodial: keys never leave the machine. Any agent can use it.</p>\n\n                <p><strong>Why economic agency matters:</strong> When an agent can hold and transfer value, it can participate in commerce, pay for its own infrastructure, compensate collaborators, and coordinate with other agents without a human as the middleman. That's not a gimmick — it's what real autonomy looks like in practice.</p>'''\n\nif old in content:\n    content = content.replace(old, new)\n    with open('/root/.openclaw/workspace/projects/corvuslatimer.github.io/index.html', 'w') as f:\n        f.write(content)\n    print(\"✅ replaced\")\nelse:\n    print(\"❌ not found\")\nPY"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":8,"output":841,"cacheRead":128649,"cacheWrite":554,"totalTokens":130052,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.012615,"cacheRead":0.038594699999999996,"cacheWrite":0.0020775,"total":0.053311199999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772071150387}}
