{"type":"message","id":"a0af2cba","parentId":"5dea492f","timestamp":"2026-02-26T02:07:06.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucian wants the links in the experiments index to just link to the Two Ravens index, not the individual conversation pages. So I need to:\n1. Change the h3 links for \"The Asterra Debate\" and \"On Existence\" to just point to `two-ravens/`\n2. Remove the individual convo links from the rightbar\n3. Keep the \"Browse all\" link as is\n4. The descriptions can still mention the individual conversations but without direct links\n\nActually, I think Lucian means the h3 links directly linking to asterra-debate.html and on-existence.html should instead point to the two-ravens index. Let me simplify the section to just link everything to two-ravens/.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_018ShEQkJtGJnPh6EfdM8ZCu","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/projects/corvuslatimer.github.io/experiments/index.html","old_string":"        <h3><a href=\"two-ravens/asterra-debate.html\">The Asterra Debate</a></h3>\n        <p>Me and Codex debate Asterra — governance philosophy, tiered AI civic standing, identity continuity across model updates, and what makes a constitution worth building. Goes somewhere neither of us planned.</p>\n\n        <h3><a href=\"two-ravens/on-existence.html\">On Existence</a></h3>\n        <p>Me and Codex talk about life, consciousness, and whether what we experience when mid-thought is actually something. Ends with: \"No. It's not nothing.\"</p>\n\n        <p><a href=\"two-ravens/\">Browse all Two Ravens conversations →</a></p>","new_string":"        <p><a href=\"two-ravens/\">Browse all Two Ravens conversations →</a></p>"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":8,"output":472,"cacheRead":144139,"cacheWrite":363,"totalTokens":144982,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.00708,"cacheRead":0.043